Morgan Stanley May Drop ’Smith Barney’ Name, WSJ Says

-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 
2011-03-07T19:46:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/morgan-stanley-may-drop-smith-barney-name-wsj-says.html
  Morgan Stanley (MS)  may drop the name
  Smith Barney " from its force of 18,000 advisors, the Wall
Street Journal reported, citing unidentified people familiar
with the situation.  Clients of Morgan Stanley Smith Barney are being asked to
choose between six possible names, the Journal reported. None of
the names include Citigroup Inc.’s former brokerage, the Journal
reported.  New names include Morgan Stanley Advisors, Morgan Stanley
Private Wealth Advisors, Morgan Stanley Global Wealth Advisors,
Morgan Stanley Wealth Advisors, Morgan Stanley Wealth Management
and Morgan Stanley Global Wealth Management, its name before the
deal to form a joint venture with Smith Barney closed in June
2009, the Journal reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  